The head of the ISC (Superior Audit Institution for Public Finance) said: "The control of pseudo self-employment (in Czech " Švarc system") has failed because of politicians.
In the area of public procurement, the Czech Republic has competent inspectors and high-quality legislation but is lagging behind in its implementation.
This was stated by Miloslav Kala, the Vice-President of the Supreme Audit Institution for Public Finance, in an interview for Aktuálně.cz.
