Every week, a new file arrives on my desk.
Imitators only need a few more letters to register their marks.
Thus, instead of Gucci, Lu-Gucci is recorded, and instead of Prada, Prada-Kny is recorded.
German companies are also being legally copied, such as Puma, the manufacturer of sports goods.
Pattloch opens a binder in which the recordings made at the Beijing trademark office are located.
On September 14, 2010, a Chinese company registered the brand Zegna DF Puma, a name that the company artificially created by taking over part of the name Ermenegildo Zegna, the fashion house.
