The drink kills the smell.
I'm trying a few pieces.
If you can avoid putting it under your nose, it's not bad - it sounds like a sushi that would have spent long hours on a bus.
The rakfisk dates back to a period when Norway was poor, before the invention of refrigeration, the fish was immersed in airtight water barrels and then salted in autumn.
